# Backup Pi configuration
# Copy this file, fill in the values, then run:
#   sudo bash setup-backup-pi.sh /path/to/backup-pi.conf
#
# Threat model: this file holds NO borg passphrases and NO kopia secrets.
# Physical theft of the Pi must not yield decryptable data. Backups are
# encrypted with passphrases held in Infisical on the manager host; the
# manager (neuromancer) injects them per-operation via SSH SendEnv.

# Admin user on the Pi (the user that owns scripts and backup keys).
# Default matches the Raspberry Pi Imager username from docs/SETUP-BACKUP-PI.md.
ADMIN_USER="piadmin"

# ── Tailscale ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The auth key MUST be:
#   (a) REUSABLE — single-use keys are consumed on first join. A drive
#       replacement that re-runs this script with a single-use key fails.
#   (b) NOT ephemeral — ephemeral nodes auto-expire on disconnect.
#   (c) Tagged with `tag:backup-target` — required for the ACL setup
#       (see docs/SETUP-BACKUP-PI.md "Tailscale ACLs"). Without this tag
#       on the key, Tailscale rejects the Pi's --advertise-tags claim.
# Generate at https://login.tailscale.com/admin/settings/keys with:
#   Reusable: ON   Ephemeral: OFF   Tags: tag:backup-target
TAILSCALE_AUTH_KEY="CONFIGURE_ME"
TAILSCALE_HOSTNAME="backup-pi"

# ── Clients (whitespace-separated list) ──────────────────────────
#
# For every name listed here, set CLIENT_<UPPERNAME>_PUBKEY and
# CLIENT_<UPPERNAME>_REPO_PATH below. Per-client passphrases and
# freshness/HC URLs live on the manager (neuromancer's
# ~/containers/scripts/borg-pi-manage.conf), not here.
#
# Each name must match [a-z0-9-]+ (used as a directory suffix and validated
# by borg-serve-only.sh).
CLIENTS="neuromancer wintermute"

# ── neuromancer (this host backs itself up to the Pi) ──
# REPO_PATH stays at /mnt/backup/borg (legacy path — kept to avoid moving
# data). New clients should follow the /mnt/backup/borg-<name> convention.
CLIENT_NEUROMANCER_PUBKEY="CONFIGURE_ME"
CLIENT_NEUROMANCER_REPO_PATH="/mnt/backup/borg"

# ── wintermute (Linux desktop, runs borgmatic) ──
CLIENT_WINTERMUTE_PUBKEY="CONFIGURE_ME"
CLIENT_WINTERMUTE_REPO_PATH="/mnt/backup/borg-wintermute"

# ── Manager SSH key ──────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Public key of the management-path SSH key on the manager host. The Pi's
# /home/borg/.ssh/authorized_keys gets a line forcing
#   /usr/local/bin/borg-manage.sh
# under this key — the manager (neuromancer) drives prune / check / list /
# restore-test by SSHing with this key and SendEnv BORG_PASSPHRASE.
#
# Generate on the manager (as the user that will run cron — chrisl8):
#   ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -f ~/.ssh/borg-pi-mgmt -N "" -C "neuromancer-borg-pi-mgmt"
# Then paste the contents of ~/.ssh/borg-pi-mgmt.pub here.
MANAGER_SSH_PUBKEY="CONFIGURE_ME"

# ── USB drive ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DRIVE_DEVICE="/dev/sda"
DRIVE_LABEL="backupdrive"
MOUNT_POINT="/mnt/backup"

# ── Web admin RPC (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────
#
# When set, the script provisions a 'webadmin' user whose SSH key is forced
# to invoke /usr/local/bin/pi-rpc.sh — a dispatcher that whitelists `status`,
# `apt-upgrade`, and `reboot`. Borg-related verbs (check/prune) are NOT
# routed through this path; the web admin uses the manager key for those,
# fetching passphrases from Infisical the same way borg-pi-manage.sh does.
#
# Leave as CONFIGURE_ME to skip the web admin RPC setup entirely.
#
# Generate on the web-admin host:
#   ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -f ~/.ssh/backup-pi-webadmin -N ""
# Then paste the contents of ~/.ssh/backup-pi-webadmin.pub here.
WEBADMIN_SSH_PUBKEY="CONFIGURE_ME"

# ── sshd hardening (always-on, no flag) ──────────────────────────
# The setup script unconditionally installs an sshd_config drop-in with
# PasswordAuthentication=no, PermitRootLogin=no, AllowUsers <admin> borg
# [webadmin], and AcceptEnv BORG_PASSPHRASE / BORG_PASSPHRASE_*. fail2ban
# is installed with an sshd jail. Tailscale-only access is enforced by UFW
# (not by ListenAddress — that caused a boot-time race in an earlier
# revision). No tunable flag for any of this.
#
# Also unconditional: /etc/sudoers.d/010_pi-nopasswd and
# /etc/sudoers.d/90-cloud-init-users (the Pi Imager / cloud-init NOPASSWD
# entries for ADMIN_USER) are REMOVED. Future re-runs of setup-backup-pi.sh
# prompt for piadmin's password. SET A STRONG ONE before disconnecting.
